#=GF CC   VapB is the antitoxin of a bacterial toxin-antitoxin gene pair.
#=GF CC   The cognate toxin is VapC, Pfam:PF05016. The family contains
#=GF CC   several related antitoxins from Cyanobacteria and
#=GF CC   Actinobacterial families. Antitoxins of this class carry an
#=GF CC   N-terminal ribbon-helix-helix domain, RHH, that is highly
#=GF CC   conserved across all type II bacterial antitoxins, which
#=GF CC   dimerises with the RHH domain of a second VapB molecule. A hinge
#=GF CC   section follows the RHH, with an additional pair of flexible
#=GF CC   alpha helices at the C-terminus. This C-terminus is the
#=GF CC   Toxin-binding region of the dimer, and so is specific to the
#=GF CC   cognate toxin, whereas the RHH domain has the specific function
#=GF CC   of lying across the RNA-binding groove of the toxin dimer and
#=GF CC   inactivating the active-site - a more general function of all
#=GF CC   antitoxins.
